<font color="#FF0000">VIETNAM VETS</font><br>
<tt>Sat Jan  4 20:48:41 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I served 19 months in SVN as a Marine Recon platoon leader.<br>
My memories of most of it, as I think most combat vets will <br>
attest, are primarily hours of boredom punctuated by minutes<br>
of abject terror.<br><br>
The people had as many different opinions of us and our right/reason to be there<br>
as we seem to have of them.  Many of us who had to make assaults with ARVN troops<br>
remember having to throw them out of the helos and forcing them to fight at the point<br>
of our own guns. I do not shed many tears for most of the SVN's<br>
I knew. I am sure that those of them who remember me do not do so fondly.<br>
We were at war, even if many of them were not.<br><br>
As to the Hollywood versions of Vietnam, Full Metal Jacket most <br>
closely parallels my own time and experiences.  AppocNow was pure fiction<br>
and not very good fiction. Oliver Stone is full of it despite <br>
his claims of having served there, Platoon had a few valid <br>
points the rest was self serving commercialism designed to<br>
sell his book.<br><br>
Happy New Year to all and Semper Fi to my mates<br>
DME1118@aol.com
